<subSubSection id="06AD6573CB411F34FF1DBDEE007BF97F" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4E0836F8CB411F34FF1DBDEE007BF97F" blockId="7.[151,1436,1523,1764]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FF1DBDEE003EF9B3" bold="true" box="[151,273,1523,1548]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="89B74D7BCB411F34FD94BDE8035AF9B3" authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[542,629,1524,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FD94BDE8035AF9B3" box="[542,629,1524,1548]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the wing pattern and the male genitalia features (see diagnosis under that species). 
<taxonomicName id="89B74D7BCB411F34FEBEBE04037DF98F" authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1957" box="[308,594,1560,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rubromarginata" subSpecies="indica">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FEBEBE04037DF98F" box="[308,594,1560,1584]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. rubromarginata indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from the nominate subspecies by larger size, and some differences in the wing pattern and the male genitalia. In 
<taxonomicName id="89B74D7BCB411F34FC93BE20051BF9EB" authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1957" box="[793,1076,1596,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rubromarginata" subSpecies="indica">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FC93BE20051BF9EB" box="[793,1076,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. rubromarginata indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ground colour of the wings and the shadow on the forewing from apex to the middle of the inner margin is paler than in the nominate subspecies. The posterior margins of the uncus lobes are truncate, and their apical angles are less swollen than in the nominate subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
